@@row
  \card{Empiricism Returns}{### **Finite-state Models Redux: 1983-1993** 
Finite-state models began to receive attention again after work on finite-state phonology and morphology by Kaplan and Kay (1981) and finite-state models of syntax by Church (1980).

Return of empiricism; most notably the rise of probabilistic models throughout speech and langauge processing, influenced thoroughly by the work at IBM Thomas J. Watson Research Center on probablistic models of speech recognition.

These probabilisitic methods are other such data-driven approaches spread into part-of-speech tagging, parsing and attachment ambiguities, and [connectionist](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connectionism) approaches from speech recognition to semantics. }
@@ @@
